@NODE INFORMATION "DMC Information"

  Information:
  ~~~~~~~~~~~~

  Early  in  1994  I  came  across  an  ASCII reader source code file and
  decided to update it with a host of new features.    Then I came across
  a  program  named  MAGNUM which was a wicked utility !    (Very bugged,
  but wicked !)

  I  contacted  the author of Magnum, neamely Wai Hung Lui, and asked him
  if  there  was to be any Bug Free versions released.    The answer ....
  NO !    :(

  However,  Wai  decided  to  release  the source code via F1 LICENCEWARE
  along with an updated version of Magnum.    So I bought the source code
  from there and had a look at it !   Hmmm.   Where were the nasty bugs ?
  Aha found em !

  To  cut  a very long story short, I eventually managed to get the whole
  thing  up  and running and released it as a new Disk Mag Creator by the
  name of DMC back in early 1994.

  The  Shareware  release  sold  pretty well and I got a load of feedback
  from  registered  users  and took all their comments and suggestions on
  board.

  A  couple  of  months  later,  three  new  DELUXE  versions of DMC were
  released  along with an Article Tester Utility.    Wow, how the punters
  loved them !

  Then I started releasing special coded versions to various PD Libraries
  for  use  with their catalogues.    Over the last year I have even been
  involved  with a few disk mags.    This lead me to update the code even
  more and a whole host of new special features were added to the code.

  Now  almost  a total re-write from the original Magnum Code !    (I kid
  you  not  -  if you don't believe me, send me Ł10 and I'll sell you the
  source)

  Above  all,  every suggestion from Registered users of DMC & DMC Deluxe
  were taken on board and coded into this release.


  The result .... THE ULTIMATE DMC .... The final !


