@NODE CONFIGURATION "DMC Creating The Configuration File"

  CREATING THE CONFIGURATION FILE:
  ~~~~~~~~ ~~~ ~~~~~~~~~~~~~ ~~~~~

  DMC works by reading a text file DMC.Config from disk.

  If  you have just updated from the PD Version of DMC or from a previous
  old  version,  then  please  note  that the configuration file for this
  version has altered slightly!

  Please see @{"THOSE UPDATING" link NEW_USERS}

  The  file  can  be edited via any text editor and must be saved back to
  disk in ASCII format and called DMC.Config

  This file will tell DMC where to look for all your text and iff files.

  It  is  easy  to  create and I'm sure you will be creating Disk Mags or
  Catalogue Disks etc.    in no time at all.    :)

  You  can  create  your own configuration file by either editing the one
  that comes with DMC or just start your very own from scratch.

