@NODE SECRET_CONVERTER "DMC The Secret Converter"


  What  this  util  does  is ask you to select a text file and then for a
  password.     Type  in  any  password  you  like in either UPPERCASE or
  lowercase or even a MiXtUrE ... It doesn't really matter.

  Your  file  will  be  encryted with the password so no one can view the
  file without knowing your password details.

  A second file holding details of the size of the file and password will
  be saved to disk automatically.

  Please  note that the files will be saved to disk as DMC.SECRET.asc and
  also DMC.SECRET.asc.info

  DMC won't recognise the files if they are renamed !!!

  When  you  select  the  SECRET button via DMC, it will search for these
  files and if they are present, will ask you to input the password.  (it
  even tells you how many letters are required) :)

  If  the  correct password is typed in, then the file will be loaded and
  de-crypted and displayed as normal.

  Passwords can contain spaces so your password could even be "Andy Gee!"

  At  this  present time, I have a neat idea to include the Encryption of
  files into the @{"TESTER" link TESTER} ,but as yet have not implemented it.

  If I get around to it, I will add it to it !  Hold on ... I have !!! :)


