@NODE IFF "DMC Creating IFF Pictures"

  CREATING IFF FILES:
  ~~~~~~~~ ~~~ ~~~~~~

  Mostly  all paint packages will save in IFF and most of us I think will
  have  a  copy of .... din din daaaa ..... Captain C a a v e m a a n !!!

  I  mean  DPAINT  ;-) Yes it is pretty out of date now compared to other
  paint and presentation packages, but we all use it, don't we ?

  Pictures can be in any resolution except AGA (A1200 / A4000) modes.

  These are not supported yet but maybe at a later date.  Who knows ?

  Please  note that the viewing area of the picture is restricted to NTSC
  size !    eg.    320 by 200 for low res or 640 by 200 for hi-res.

  This  is so the picture will fit inside the display area of DMC between
  the  top  info  bar  and the user panel.    You don't have to save your
  picture(s)  as  NTSC size.    In other words, only the first 200 pixels
  will be shown on screen.

  Just  load  the  example  pictures  into  your  paint  package for more
  details.     (They  contain full details on what to do, so load them in
  before you start to draw your own - it makes sense)


  @{"MAIN INDEX" link MAIN}


@ENDNODE

@NODE INTRO "DMC The Intro Pictures"

  CREATING INTRO PICS:
  ~~~~~~~~ ~~~~~ ~~~~~

  Draw your pictures and save them to disk as DMC.Pic1, DMC.Pic2 and
  DMC.Pic3.

  These can be in any resolution except AGA !

  Please  remember  that the bigger the resolution - the bigger the space
  used on disk and also more memory is used !

  These files do NOT have to be present on the disk. You may only want to
  include one Intro Pic or NONE !  It's up to you really.

  New  to this version of DMC is the ability to use any background colour
  for  your  Intro  Pics and it will fill the screen !    Previously only
  black  could  be  used.     Don't forget that the Intro Pics can now be
  skipped by pressing either mouse button or any Keyboard key.


  @{"MAIN INDEX" link MAIN}


@ENDNODE

@NODE PANEL "DMC The User Panel"

  CREATING THE USER PANEL:
  ~~~~~~~~ ~~~ ~~~~ ~~~~~~

  Please  load  the  file  named  Panel.Example into your favourite paint
  package.    Use this as a Stencil to create your own.
  (This file can be found in the EXAMPLES drawer)

  The  example  is  in  Hi-Res  and must remain in the same resolution in
  order for DMC to recognise it.

  When  you have finished, pick up the whole thing as a BRUSH and save it
