@NODE COMMANDS "DMC Keyboard And Panel Commands"

  PANEL / KEYBOARD COMMANDS:
  ~~~~~ ~ ~~~~~~~~ ~~~~~~~~~

  The  Panel  contains  no  less  than  14 buttons which can be selected.
  All of these also have keyboard options added too.

  Pressing HELP whilst using DMC will give a full list of them.

  All  buttons  can  be  selected  using  either  the left or right mouse
  button.


  Please  note  that  if you select the CLI button, this will either take
  you  to the CLI or WBench depending on where you loaded DMC from.    To
  return to DMC, simply press Left Amiga & A.

  This  is  a  NEW  feature  to  this  version  of  DMC. To keep it fully
  multi-tasking  all  processor (CPU) time is returned to the system when
  you  are  in CLI or WBench.    Now you can use DMC along side any other
  Multi-Tasking program.  Isn't the Amiga a wonderful machine ?


  Another  NEW  feature  is  that  let's say you are on the First page of
  either  an  article or the Index.    Previously if you pressed FIRST or
  PREV, then that page would be shown again !    Not anymore.    In other
  words,  options on the panel will now only function if they can be used
  succesfully !

  (by the way, the same applies to keyboard options also)

  The button(s) will say OK if option can be selected.

  Don't worry about all that too much as it's not really important !


  @{"MAIN INDEX" link MAIN}


