@NODE DMC_RTDD "DMC Goes Compatible With CMania Files"

  DMC_RTDD.exe  is a special version of DMC which automatically runs @{"RTDD" link RTDD}
  (Real Time Data Decruncher) when loaded.

  This  means  that  DMC  will  be  compatible with all files packed with
  @{"Crunch-Mania" link CRUNCHMANIA}

  The  old  registered  versions of DMC were not compatible with crunched
  files and had to have @{"RTDD" link RTDD} run in the startup-sequence.

  eg.

  RTDD
  DMC.exe

  However,  all  that  has  changed  now  as  this  new  version  of  DMC
  automatically runs @{"RTDD" link RTDD} from memory.

  RTDD  is no  longer  required on the disk as DMC holds it in memory and
  automatically copies it to ram: on loading.   The only file required to
  keep  DMC  compatible is the Crunch-Mania Library (CRM.Library) in your
  Libs Directory.

  If this file cannot be found then DMC will report this and give you the
  option  to have the file saved to your libs directory.    If you decide
  not  to  copy  it  to  your libs directory, then DMC won't run @{"RTDD" link RTDD} and
  therefore it won't be compatible with files packed with @{"Crunch-Mania" link CRUNCHMANIA}

  I  have  added  this to DMC as it had been requested by many registered
  users of past versions.

  However,  if  you  do not plan to use any packers, then I have supplied
  another adapted version of DMC for you.

  Please  note  that  there  is another version of DMC on this disk which
  does not run RTDD etc.  Please see @{"DMC.exe" link DMC_EXE}


  @{"MAIN INDEX" link MAIN}


@ENDNODE

@NODE DMC_EXE "DMC The Other Version"


  This  version  of  DMC  is  not  compatible  with  files  crunched with
  Crunch-Mania due to the fact that it does not run @{"RTDD" link RTDD} when loaded !

  This  way,  you have the option not to use @{"Crunch-Mania" link CRUNCHMANIA} but instead you
  could use PowerPacker to crunch your file.

  Obviously DMC isn't compatible with crunched files, but that problem is
  easily solved by using a real time data decruncher.

  Let's say you have used PowerPacker to crunch all your pics, text etc.

  First  of  all  you will require the utility named Power Packer Patcher
  which  should  be  available  from most PD Libraries.    (You will also
  require the PowerPacker.Library)

  All  you  need  to  do  is run PPatcher in your Startup-Sequence before
  launching  DMC  and all your crunched files will be compatible.

  eg. (your startup-sequence)

  PPatcher
  DMC.exe

  In  my  view  (and many others), PowerPacker is a great packer, but you
  may be interested to learn that @{"Crunch-Mania" link CRUNCHMANIA} gives a far better packing
  ratio and @{"RTDD" link RTDD} is compatible with all Amigas.

  If  you  wish  to  use Crunch-Mania to pack all your files, then please
  note  that  there  is  a  version  of  DMC  on this disk which is fully
  compatible with these type of files.   See @{"DMC_RTDD" link DMC_RTDD}


  @{"MAIN INDEX" link MAIN}


@ENDNODE

@NODE CRUNCHMANIA "The Best Packer On The Amiga - Crunch Mania"

  I  have  been using this packer for about one year now and so have many
  others  that I know such as LSD, AMOSZINE, LOGIC PD and mostly everyone
  who has used past versions of DMC.

  It  is  a  neat  utility  that  crunches  files  to a smaller file size
  (sometimes over 50% smaller) thus saving you valuable disk space.

  Any  file used by DMC can be crunched with this packer such as all your
  text files and pictures and music.

  I'll  type  in  a  quick  guide on how to use Crunch-Mania to pack your
  files.  However, please note that this is not the complete instructions
  which can be found with the full Crunch-Mania package.

  First of all Load Crunch-Mania

  Click On DATA (*IMPORTANT*)

  Click On LOAD

  Click On Crunch

  The file will be packed for you.

  Now all you have to do is save the file back to disk.


  If  for some reason you want to de-crunch the file back to normal, then
  the process is as follows:

  Load Crunch-Mania

  Click on DATA

  Click On LOAD

  Choose   a  crunched  file  which  will  be  loaded  and  automatically
  de-crucnhed for you.

  Click On SAVE and save the file to disk.

  (You do not have to click on CRUNCH)


  Please  note  that  if  you  plan  to crunch Reloc (exe) files with the
  shareware  version of CMania, then you won't be able to de-crunch these
  files with it !

  You  shouldn't  have  any use for Reloc files as DMC only requires DATA
  files such as Text, Pics and Music etc.

  If you want to use CMania to the full, then I suggest you register with
  the  author today.    I have been using the full registered version for
  almost a year and it was the best purchase I have made yet.

  Thanx for an excellent utility Thomas.  Cheers :)


  @{"RTDD" link RTDD}
