@ENDNODE

@NODE RTDD "Real Time Data Decruncher - RTDD"

  RTDD is a neat utility that comes with @{"Crunch-Mania" link CRUNCHMANIA}

  What  it  does  is trick the computer into thinking that these crunched
  files are in fact normal un-crunched files !

  Therefore making any program compatible with these type of files.

  Let's  say you had crunched a load of picture (IFF) files and wanted to
  load them into your paint program.   Obviously they could not be loaded
  in  as the program won't be compatible with these.    However, a simple
  run of RTDD sets things straight !

  eg. (In your Startup-Sequence)


  RTDD
  DPaintIV

  Now  the  same applies to DMC, but you don't have to run RTDD from your
  startup-sequence  as  there  is  a  special version of DMC on this disk
  which automatically runs RTDD from memory (not from disk)

  See @{"DMC_RTDD" link DMC_RTDD}


  @{"MAIN INDEX" link MAIN}


@ENDNODE

@NODE AGAS "The Name You Can Trust"

  The  AGAS name has been used for ALL my productions over the last three
  years or so and is now a well know name (believe it or not)

  As you know it stands for Andy Gibson's Amiga Software, but back in the
  early days it stood for   Andy, George, Andy & Stevie.

  We were  just a bunch of guys doing the usual demo stuff and eventually
  Stevie  and  George  split  the  scene  and AGAS was left with only two
  members!

  We were Andy Gibson & Andy Strachan.    So we just used our initials to
  form the same name (AGAS).

  After  a  year  or  so,  Andy  Strachan  decided to leave the Amiga and
  purchase a PC !  :(

  So I had to change the name of AGAS ?  Nah, you know what it stands for
  now.

  So  it  has  served well as a name and one I will certainly stick with.

  For  1995  it has been altered slightly to AGAS Productions as it has a
  more professional approach,  just like I have with all my new projects.

  How do you pronounce AGAS ?

  Well, like this ... eh-gas !    Simple and not as most people think ...
  ah-gas.

  Just  thought some of you may be interested to know where the name AGAS
  originally  came  from.     (as if ya care !)

  l8rs dudes  ;-)


